incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sphinx 4
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to follow your own lead and be in the moment. You are transfixed by the now and your way of doing things. This self absorption is your individual contribution to the world. While it is not your intention to give others direction, you do. By following your heart and doing your own expressive thing, others can find direction through your example and will follow. Do your own thing and make sure it is your passion to your core.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Self-Expression
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy of self expression. You are here to be different and do your own thing. It is through individual expression that the rest of us can look on and adapt to the new ideas that we feel resonance with. Understand though that individualism is not always adaptive and some self expression will drive others away. It is the nature of the energy and it is not personal.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Defiance 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross brings the energy that stands up to controlling influences. You are here to embody self expression. There will be people that attempt to impose rules of just how you can do that. Your energy is to defy those rules because how can anyone put bounds on self expression? You are here to make sure your expression has a voice and no one can box that in.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sphinx 2
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of this Cross is to see and be open to the possibilities. You are here to guide us by showing us the many possible directions and ways to create a beautiful world. You point out the many possible roads we may choose to take or give suggestions for alternate routes. However, you may have difficulty explaining why to take that suggested route.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of the Driver
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross will give you direction in your life. That direction is going to be tied to discovering the truth -- your truth, the truth of those around you and perhaps universal truths. This energy will give you consistent direction in your life and you will try to pull those around you forward toward that destiny of knowing the Truth.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Defiance
incarnation_crosses.description: Whether conscious of this energy or not, you are here to step out of line and to represent the 'other' way of doing things. Your perceived defiance may be small or great but your goal here is to bring about variations from the norm. Most of the time this will result in slight variances coming into acceptance. This occurs not from your action but rather from the perception of your action by others.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Laws
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy that drives you to have laws. As a young child with this Cross if there were not rules and laws in your house, you may have found the scenario disturbing. This Cross is about living out the laws of the tribe. The lead energy has mutative qualities so there is the drive to make the laws better, but this is not revolutionary energy. The lead energy has more of a gradual change, as the law has limitations. If these limitations were to change drastically, it would feel like chaos.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Mutation
incarnation_crosses.description: This Cross carries the energy to cause mutation or change. These changes are generally associated with rules or laws. There may be some moral judgment as any time you try to change law you may be perceived as a dissident. If you make the change from the position of power you may be perceived as being corrupt. But you are here to be a mutative force in changing the tribal rules and laws.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Wishes
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy to provide leadership for change in the law and the way things operate. This is always going to create tension as there will always be those who wish for things to stay the same and those wishing for change. This Cross is about wishing and hoping for a better future. You are here to make that wish for the future and provide some leadership to make it happen.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Explanation 3
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is driven by the energy of the 4th gate which is 'the answer', but this answer is really just a theory that has to be expressed and then verified. You are here to explain your theories and this is a bit of a challenge. The explanation you give will be individualistic and for a logical theory to be accepted, it needs to appeal to the collective. Your mission is to give the rest of us an uncommon explanation, one that most of us wouldn't think of.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Formulization
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to express your theories about patterns and formulas that explain things. You are not here to back them up, but to lay them out for the rest of us to puzzle over.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Revolution 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is about revolution that is practical. If the pattern of the revolution fits and is supported by facts, then it is a change that you are willing to invest in.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Consciousness 4
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to be in the flow of life. All of life is made up of patterns that dance in the river of time. Your energy is the basis of these patterns.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Habits
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross brings the energy of patterns and habits and you are here to have a strong influence on those patterns. At times you may be very rigid about these things, but what you offer the rest of the world is that by having patterns, you can find individual rhythm.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Separation 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy that wants to march to its own beat. This is energy that is looking for patterns and rhythms that work for you and not necessarily anyone else.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Eden 3
incarnation_crosses.description: So you were thrown out of Eden, or at least that may be what birth felt like to you. Many who carry this Cross enter the world reluctantly as the womb provides everything that is needed.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Conflict
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy you bring to this life is about finding your opportunity through the relationships you establish. The conflict that you have to endure is finding balance between feeling tossed out of the Garden of Eden and finding joy living on the earthly plane.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of the Plane 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to be an earthly guide. The energy of your Cross is about life on the earthly plane.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sphinx 3
incarnation_crosses.description: As the Cross of the sphinx you bring leadership to guide and direct as your energy supports vision for the future.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Interaction
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is driven to be involved in leadership. This is not necessarily taking the lead but may manifest as an individual contributor to something bigger.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Masks 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is expected to lead when there is a dire need for someone to step forward and provide a solution.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Contagion 2
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is to be a contributor through your individual effort. Your passion and expression of excitement is contagious.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Contribution
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of this Cross is to make your contribution to society through demonstration.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Uncertainty
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross provides you with the desire to get the right house, the right plot of land and all sorts of nice things.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Planning 4
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to contribute planning for your family, group or community.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Focus
incarnation_crosses.description: You are driven with the energy to find focus in things, especially around planning.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Identification 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries the energy to have great focus and contribution.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Vessel of Love 4
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is based in love. Love of spirit, love of the body, love of humanity and love of the self.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Behavior
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy to guide and correct the behavior of others.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Prevention 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries the energy to examine behavior.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Eden 4
incarnation_crosses.description: We come into body from the ethereal world that has a lightness and a lack of density.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Ideas
incarnation_crosses.description: You are apt to be driven to express your ideas.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Education 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the Cross of Education and the energy that supports the value of education.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Eden 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy and drive to go and explore the world -- but it really isn't just about you.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Articulation
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries a special energy to be able to spread the word.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Education
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to educate by way of the lecture.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sphinx
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to be intuitive about the past.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Listening
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to listen and collect the history of events and episodes in this life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Masks 2
incarnation_crosses.description: As the Left Angle Cross of Masks, you are here to look at the past and give direction through your own mutative process.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Contagion 2
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is to be a contributor through your individual effort.

incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is to be a contributor through your individual effort.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Contribution
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of this Cross is to make your contribution to society through demonstration.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Uncertainty
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross provides you with the desire to get the right house, the right plot of land and all sorts of nice things.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Service
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross brings four logical energies together. The lead energy is opinion. With opinion energy, there is a great drive to correct and organize things so you can live a healthy, longer, and more joyful life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Opinions
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to give opinions. Not all of your opinions are going to be popular and you are not always going to be right. But, your opinions are important to help correct behavior.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Upheaval
incarnation_crosses.description: With your Cross, your purpose is to get your hands dirty, muck about and stir things up.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Service 3
incarnation_crosses.description: You bring energy that says 'get your stuff together'. The lead energy here is correction and this correction is about making life better and more joyful.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Correction
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to correct patterns and discover a more joyful life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Upheaval 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to stir things up. Your Cross brings the energy to turn things over in an effort to make things better.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Four Ways 4
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is driven by the energy to make sure everyone has what they need.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Need
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the need to be expressive. This energy is very creative, but there is a strong desire for this creativity to be done in private.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Refinement 2
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross provides direction about what is needed.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sleeping Phoenix 2
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy you carry is about being busy. It doesn't matter what you are doing, you just know that being busy is what you need to be.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of the Now
incarnation_crosses.description: This Cross carries the energy of being in the present moment. It also carries the energy of family and community.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Duality
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to be the mutative force in the tribe.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Tension
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries the energy of tension that is necessary to maintain order in a tribal environment.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Control
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy of needing control. It is through this control that you can take something and recreate it as something new.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Endeavour
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy in your Cross is about coming together in a very controlled way to make something bigger happen.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Rulership
incarnation_crosses.description: Fueled by the energies of listening, educating, and figuring things out, you have the energy to rule your world.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Grace
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the design of being a listener, and you love to listen.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Informing
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the great gift of the energy to listen and the energy to communicate.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Explanation 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to vocalize individual expression.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Assimilation
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy that pushes you to bring forward individual ideas to create change.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Dedication
incarnation_crosses.description: There is a drive in your Cross to provide the same explanation over and over again.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Four Ways
incarnation_crosses.description: You are driven to know and have a mental understanding of all that you encounter in life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Rationalization
incarnation_crosses.description: You carry the energy that allows you to be incredibly gifted with grasping concepts and truly understanding them.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Incarnation
incarnation_crosses.description: You carry the energy of the process of incarnation.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Vessel of Love
incarnation_crosses.description: At the very center of all your energies is love.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Innocence
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to be an influence on the world about bringing forward the love of life and living.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Healing
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is to communicate the value of being healthy and its necessity for a joyful life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Rulership 4
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy to promote yourself as a leader.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of the Trickster
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy of 'slight of hand'.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Confrontation 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy to confront rulership and impose rulership of your own.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Unexpected
incarnation_crosses.description: As a tribal Cross, you are here to support and stand for your tribe.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Caring
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to bring a sense of caring for all things and all people.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Alignment
incarnation_crosses.description: You carry the energy to handle the unexpected in amazingly smooth ways.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Unexpected 3
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy to struggle with things in this lifetime.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Risks
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is that of a gambler.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Alignment 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here with the energy to make a shift from the old, traditional paradigm and align with the new.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Contagion 3
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries the energy to say 'yes'.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Commitment
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to say 'yes' and be committed to many things.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Industry 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to do things and can find yourself busy all the time.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Contagion
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross carries the energy of desire and to experience what you desire.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Fates
incarnation_crosses.description: You carry the energy of drive and obsession.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Industry
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of this Cross is to be industrious.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Unexpected 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You carry the energy that is likely to land you in a place of leadership rather unexpectedly.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Influence
incarnation_crosses.description: You have the energy to be very influential with others because you have the energy to be persistent.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of the Alpha
incarnation_crosses.description: This is the Cross of a leader.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Maya 3
incarnation_crosses.description: This Cross has the energy of survival by looking for value.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Conservation
incarnation_crosses.description: The energy of your Cross is to conserve and preserve life.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Limitation 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy of knowing limitation in order to survive or achieve preservation.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Four Ways 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross is driven by the lead energy which is looking for privacy.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Retreat
incarnation_crosses.description: Your energy is about the right for everyone to have their own little place of retreat.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Refinement
incarnation_crosses.description: You bring the energy of having your own living space and nice things within it.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of the Sleeping Phoenix 4
incarnation_crosses.description: Your energy has a great need to be busy.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Power
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross brings a lot of power and energy.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Left Angle Cross of Duality 2
incarnation_crosses.description: Your Cross has the energy to thrive both individually and as part of a community.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Right Angle Cross of Consciousness 2
incarnation_crosses.description: You are here to balance the energies of desire to have an experience and be done with it.

incarnation_crosses.name: The Juxtaposition Cross of Experience
incarnation_crosses.description: You are driven to have very specific and unique experiences.
